page.title: 06North Burlingham
page.content: North Burlingham is a quiet and small place, not very modern,not so vintage; so-so I should say. It has farms, houses a few tracks and roads and a bowling green. It was difficult to find people to interview, most people are out at work during the day. One house we went to the people were away but their great big dog was there though. It jumped up and licked my face. It ran on to the rest and the rest made a fuss of it. We all went back to the minibus and the dog followed us into the minibus as Mr Gleeson was about to put his seat belt on. He went out round the back of the minibus and pulled the dog out by the scruff of the neck because it didn't go out when the said.
